snippet.textDisplay:
A lot of people are suggesting using the 70k for CV, which is fair enough and definitely a situation that needs some assistance. But as my favorite meme to come out of the CV situation says: How boomers feel about CV right now is how millennials feel about climate change all the time.

Instead of using the money for a short term problem why not use it for ong term impact. Donate to an environmental cause like Oceana or any that you believe in. There are also volunteering "vacations." You could find a good one and involve a subscriber or two as well as some strangers, get together with a company that is doing good work for a week, and make a difference. Whatever money you have left, donate to them.

Another idea that requires almost no $ - You guys live right by the beach. You could organize a yesfam beach cleanup, invite some strangers to come along, and do some good. Make sure to recycle whatever you can before sending the rest to the landfill.

Whatever you decide I'm excited to see how you'll use that money to do some good in the world.

snippet.textDisplay: I've been a huge fan of the Yes Theory philosophy since I was 20, I'm currently 23. I'm visiting Bangladesh right now. There are currently over 1200 people per square km, a lot of those whom are poverty afflicted children. Over 1/3 of children in Bangladesh drop out of school and work for pennies a day as they have no faith that school will lead them to financial stability. With your money you should come down here and speak to the kids, maybe volunteer to help youth in or even out of school... Or maybe even hire a motivation speaker. While you're down here there's a lot of things you can do such as improving their English, reaching out to the children, etc. They just need somebody to show them there is hope and I feel like you folks over at Yes Theory are very good at that type of stuff. I'd be more than willing to volunteer all of my time if you come here before I leave. I'll provide accommodations and take care of anything you may need. Thank you for reading my post.

snippet.textDisplay:
Yes Theory,
My sister is the most giving, thoughtful person who has been through a lot - not just in the past year but most of her life. She's a hilarious, quick wisecrack that moved from Seattle to, in her words, "butt-crack nowhere" Arkansas to be with her love that she met on a Grehound bus ride to a Chicago music festival. She is spontaneous and colorful and has such character. She would never accept anything for herself.
Which is why I think taking her and her boyfriend to Iceland to see the Northern Lights and maybe attend some weird music festival would be perfect. She would be so embarrassed, but I think she'd push her thoughts aside to make everyone happy (which would ultimately make her happy, too).
And, if you wanted to give her some extra dough, that wouldn't hurt!
Thanks for reading!

snippet.textDisplay: If I had 70,000 dollars I would attend a somewhat decent college to become a psychologist. I feel in America our mental health is obscenely under funded yet such a vital aspect in healthy living. Many kids are born in to abusive, toxic homes and when sent to a physiologist they are often scared to even talk for help. Growing up as one of those kids I believe we need more down to earth mental health workers who care more about the brilliance these young children poses because our future is entirely dependent upon our youth. My dream organization is called the Truth Inspired Youth. Essentially it’s a big facility where children from troubled homes can go to feel accepted and loved. My dreams for Truth Inspired Youth (TIY) is to have fully functional gyms. Playgrounds, library school and even dorms. I would want this to be 100% not for profit. I found yes theory back around one million subscribers and it has truly been a wild ride watching this Chanel grow to what it has become today. Seeking Discomfort is no longer a saying it’s a way of life for me and 5 million other subscribers. I want to give a thank you for Matt for getting that video from Tom Brady go give to them gentlemen with 3 months to live. Hands down one of my most favorite yes theory videos to date. Sending much love to the Yes Fam & Yes Fam community ❤️

snippet.textDisplay:
This is where I'd like to see the money go. Due to Corona Virus, our band has lost 14 gigs until May 15th, and that's just until then. If establishments choose to extend the date further into the future, it will be more. Some of my band mates play as full time musicians, and I really feel for them. I feel responsible, as the band manager to replace our pay somehow. I prayed as I scratched off a lottery ticket tonight, that I would win, so I could pay for the 14 gigs, but instead the Universe only gave me $20. There has been no indication that anyone cares not only about the income lost by local musicians, but all the bartenders, servers, and other kitchen staff. This is truly a sad time, and we are all scared. We don't even need the $70,000. Just give us what we lost and then find some other bands that are in the same boat. Music is all I know, and all I love, and I am truly more terrified about becoming homeless, than dying of the virus. It keeps me up at night. Life of a musician. What can I say? Music picked me.
My calculator says we lost $9,800. That's all we need. We know other bands in our area, and staffs of the establishments that are doing nothing for them, but just an apology. If you want us to pick some others to help out, we could. Most everyone else can find some kind of funding or grants to help them get through this time, but there is nothing to help for this category of employment. It almost feels like we are being labeled as dispensable. Take the fear that you had of being caught in your game, and multiply it with the feeling of your life depending on it. That's how we feel now. Then take the feeling of winning and multiply that with the feeling of saving many people from the stress and worry of how they can make it through this. That's what this would do for us.
I enjoyed the video very much. Be safe everyone.
